SendEncryptedEmailApp – Functional & Technical Overview
1. Purpose
The SendEncryptedEmailApp is a command-line utility used to send encrypted emails with configurable inputs. It enables secure, automated email delivery using file-based content and flexible recipient handling.

This tool is intended for system-generated notifications, reports, and secure communications.

2. Key Capabilities
Send encrypted emails via command line

Support multiple recipients

Accept HTML body content from a file

Allow optional SMTP configuration

Enable automation via batch scripts or schedulers

3. Command Syntax
SendEncryptedEmailApp.exe [parameters]

4. Parameters
Parameter	Required	Description
--from	Yes	Sender email address
--to	Yes	Recipient email address(es), comma-separated
--subject	Yes	Email subject line
--body	Yes	File path to HTML content
--SMTPServer	No	SMTP server hostname
--Port	No	SMTP server port
5. Example Usage
Basic Email
SendEncryptedEmailApp.exe
--from="noreply@testdomain.com"
--to="user1@testdomain.com"
--subject="Daily Report"
--body="C:\temp\report.html"

Multiple Recipients
SendEncryptedEmailApp.exe
--from="noreply@testdomain.com"
--to="user1@testdomain.com,user2@testdomain.com"
--subject="Daily Report"
--body="C:\temp\report.html"

With SMTP Configuration
SendEncryptedEmailApp.exe
--from="noreply@testdomain.com"
--to="user1@testdomain.com"
--subject="Daily Report"
--body="C:\temp\report.html"
--SMTPServer="windowsmail.mail.com"
--Port="25"

Full Example (Production)
SendEncryptedEmailApp.exe
--from="noreply@testdomain.com"
--to="user1@testdomain.com"
--subject="LicCount Report on 04/22/2026"
--body="D:\SendEncryptedEmailApp\HealthCheck\HealthCheckReport.html"
--SMTPServer="windowsmail.hhsc.texas.gov"
--Port="25"

6. Input Requirements
All required parameters (from, to, subject, body) must be provided

Body file must exist and be accessible

Email addresses must be properly formatted

SMTP server must be reachable if specified

Port must be valid and open (if specified)

7. Error Handling (Expected Behavior)
The application should validate:

Missing required parameters

Invalid or inaccessible file paths

Incorrect email formats

SMTP connectivity issues

Recommended outputs:

Clear console error messages

Exit codes for automation tracking

8. Security Considerations
Emails are encrypted before sending

Avoid storing sensitive data in plain text files

Restrict access to execution environment

Ensure SMTP servers are trusted and secure

9. Deployment & Usage
Can be executed via:

Windows Task Scheduler

Batch scripts (.bat)

Automation pipelines

Designed for Windows environments with SMTP access

10. Business Value
Automates secure email delivery

Reduces manual effort and errors

Standardizes report distribution

Supports compliance and secure communication practices

11. Potential Enhancements
